That being said it is almost exclusively a map app. I would love to see it also head in the direction of a crafting app, where you can keep track of individual  motifs, as well as see an image of it's final product per item, so you can choose style based on aesthetics.
Please add a button to toggle on and off way shrines. If it's a problem, have it set to default off. Thank you

This app has not failed me once since i've downloaded . It has everything you need regarding eso all in one place

Although the app is a wonderful idea and all together a very well done app. I think it could use improvements like adding additional content such as a more detailed map of each area, maybe a few guides on the harder dungeons and a basic overview of how the different mechanics of the game work. The app runs a little slow and it doesn't have the fastest loading in the world but all in all its a useful resource and well worth the money.

replyContent: All skyshards are available except the ones in upper craglorn. Some skyshards are located in delves and hence you need to enter the delve or use the search option to find them.

content: I NEVER have written a review for any app. ..until now. This app has been absolutely phenomenal! I have been pursuing the mages guild lorebooks for at least 6 months. Yes I went online and looked but the struggle for conveniencey bogged down my search. Now with this app all you gotta do is input the name of the book and immediately it comes up on the map! Super easy to use. One day ago I was a level 5 in mages guild now I'm a level 10. So worth the 99 cents. Thank you do much!

content: The app works well and so far no glitches. All the app does is show you the locations of skyshards and Mage's Guild lorebooks. Which is cool and useful. But you can't turn either of them off to focus on one or the other, nor can you "check" individual icons as collected to prevent unnecessary backtracking. Also, to be frank the information offered here is available for free and just a Google search away... it might only be a dollar but in the apps current condition it's not quite a dollar well-spent yet.
Simple and works.
Totes love it. It's a must have y'all.
